Skype has announced a number of major changes for its desktop and mobile applications, overhauling the platformâ€™s messaging features. The company has unveiled new messaging features which include the ability to display multiple photos and videos, preview media files, and save draft messages. Users are also able to bookmark messages and access them in a dedicated folder, and it is now much easier to send multiple photos or videos to other users. The desktop version of Skype now includes a split window option, which lets you view your contact list and messages in separate windows. These features are available on the latest version of Skype across all platforms.